```python
B1=list(Birth1.Birth_1000)
D1=list(Death1.Death_1000)
P1=list(Population1.Population)
BP=[] #Birth population for the whole each year
DP=[] #Death Population for each year
for i in range(0, len(B1)):
    BP.append((B1[i]*P1[i])/1000)
for i in range(0, len(B1)):
    DP.append((D1[i]*P1[i])/1000)  
#print(BP)
#print(DP)
```


```python
df = pd.DataFrame({'A': BP, 
                   'B': DP}, 
                  index=pd.date_range('1950', periods=71))
plt.figure()
_ = plt.boxplot([ df['A'], df['B']] )
plt.xticks([2,1], ["Birth", "Death"])
plt.title('Total Birth Rate and Total Death Rate in Poland(1950-2020)')
plt.ylabel('Number of People per year')
for spine in plt.gca().spines.values():
    plt.gca().spines['top'].set_visible(False)
plt.gca().spines['right'].set_visible(False)
```
